Klopp on Salah's heroics for Egypt: &quot;Did anybody see the video of the celebrations? I've never seen celebrations like this after 1-0!&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp on Salah: &quot;What I will say is in this moment he is our number one penalty taker! The pressure he was under was unbelievable.&quot;

Moore on Dalglish: &ldquo;In 1989, when people in this city needed him most, Kenny showed leadership beyond the call of duty in our darkest hour.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Moore: &quot;Kenny was just 38 when he and his family led Liverpool's response to Hillsborough. Families are represented here today.&quot;

Dalglish: &ldquo;It&rsquo;s great to see Sir Alex and Sir Bobby here. There&rsquo;s rivalry but there&rsquo;s never been a game when we&rsquo;ve not had a drink.&quot;<br />
<br />
Dalglish: &quot;After Hillsborough, Manchester United were one of the very first clubs to come over and show their support.&quot;

Carragher: &quot;Some say Klopp&rsquo;s job is on the line which is daft. He's done a very good job so far &amp; should be judged on realistic objectives.&quot;<br />
<br />
Carragher: &quot;Manchester United and Liverpool... one club recognised its weakness and fixed it, and the other is beset by the same problems.&quot;
